- `stalegen-smoke`: PASS
- `admission-smoke`: PASS
- `stats-smoke`: PASS
- `runtime-smoke`: PASS, 4 rows, token/event 0/0
- N=200 session gate: PASS, token/event 0/200 and 0/200

9. Design notes:
No blockers. `parse_http_request` is pure and returns `NEED_MORE` for partial input. GET body rejection is header-based (`Content-Length > 0` or `Transfer-Encoding`) so Step 7 can preserve any already-buffered post-handshake WS bytes. Duplicate headers are lowercase/comma-joined; `Connection` uses comma-token matching. `read_frame` enforces masked client-to-server frames; `write_frame` defaults unmasked for server-to-client.
